# Axionax Protocol Rule

## Architecture
- Check `packages/sdk` first for reusable business logic before implementing in apps.
- Use workspace aliases only (for example `@axionax/sdk`), never cross-package relative imports.
- Use `pnpm` for workspace dependency and script operations.

## Frontend
- Default to React Server Components; add `"use client"` only when hooks/browser APIs are required.
- Use Tailwind CSS and keep dark, cyberpunk/futuristic styling as default.
- Use `next/image` for UI images when possible.

## Integration and Reliability
- If node/validator access is unavailable, add SDK-level mock services to unblock UI development.
- Handle RPC and transaction failures gracefully with clear user-facing feedback.

## Rust Core Context
- When tasks mention Core or Node, treat it as the Rust Substrate implementation.
- Favor memory safety, predictable behavior, and performance-minded changes.

## Working Style
- Keep changes concise and practical; include TypeScript interfaces for new components.
- After edits, verify imports and workspace references remain valid.
